{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Ricotta","content":["Place milk into mixing bowl and heat <b>10 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add vinegar and heat <b>1 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>. Allow to sit in mixing bowl for 1 minute. Milk will separate into curds and whey.","Line simmering basket with a nut milk bag or 2 layers muslin cloth and set over a large bowl. Pour mixture into simmering basket and allow to drain for 30 minutes. Do not squeeze liquid from ricotta. Set drained ricotta (approx. 300-340 g) aside in a bowl. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Polenta","content":["Line a square cake tin (20 cm) with plastic wrap and set aside.","Place Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer into a seperate bowl and set aside.","Place water and stock paste into mixing bowl and bring to the boil <b>8 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add polenta and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add oil, thyme, paprika, pepper and 250 g of the reserved ricotta and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Spoon polenta mixture into prepared tin, smooth surface and place into refrigerator to set (approx. 30 minutes).","Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Remove set polenta from tin and slice into thick chips (2 x 9 cm). Place onto prepared baking tray. Sprinkle with reserved Parmesan cheese, drizzle with extra olive oil and bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C) until cheese has melted and chips are golden brown. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Ricotta","content":["1800 g full cream milk","80 g white vinegar"]},{"title":"Polenta","content":["20 g Parmesan cheese,  crust removed and cut into pieces (2 cm)","480 g water","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","150 g polenta (see Tips)","2 tsp olive oil, plus extra for baking","2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","½ tsp sweet paprika","½ tsp ground black pepper"]}],"id":"r105366","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-Wg8SkQTJIvk\/XZWaAfu-7-I\/AAAAAAAAeU0